  "texts": [
    "After a standard change of variables, it follows that Z ∼ χ 2 2N, with CDF given byF Z (z) = γ inc N, z 2 Γ(N).",
    "(8)The conditional probabilities required in (7) can be directly obtained from the CDF in (8) as followsPr(σ 2 x > γ (|h|) |σ 2 0, h) = Pr 2N σ2 x σ 2 x0 > 2N γ (|h|) σ 2 x0 σ 2 0, h = 1 -F Z 2N γ (|h|) σ 2 x0 (9)Pr(σ 2 x < γ (|h|) |σ 2 1, h) = Pr 2N σ2 x σ 2 x1 < 2N γ (|h|) σ 2 x1 σ 2 1, h = F Z 2N γ (|h|) σ 2 x1.",
    "(10)Plugging ( 9) and (10) into (7), the BEP conditioned on h can be expressed asP e (|h|) = 1 2 1 -F Z 2N γ(|h|) σ 2 x0 + F Z 2N γ(|h|) σ 2 x1.",
    "(11)The BEP can also be written as a function of the TNC parameters δ and α asP e (|h|) = 1 2 1 -F Z 2N γ(|h|) σ 2 w (1 + |h| 2 δ) + F Z 2N γ(|h|) σ 2 w (1 + |h| 2 αδ).",
    "( 12) B. TNC under Rician FadingIn this case, the channel envelope of h, R ≜ |h|, randomly changes along different coherence intervals, following a Rician distribution, whose PDF is given byf R (r) = r σ 2 s exp - r 2 + λ 2 2σ 2 s I 0 λr σ 2 s, (13)where λ denotes the amplitude of the LoS component, and σ 2 s represents the scattered power per quadrature component."
